#, no-wrap
msgid "*Dear friends*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:32
msgid ""
"My name is *Artem Vorotnikov*, and as some of you know, I have recently "
"joined the RoR development team. Today I am going to talk about the RoR "
"website goodies we have prepared for you this summer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "About current website"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:35
msgid ""
"rigsofrods.com is a dynamic website that uses a content management system "
"and several other software packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:37
msgid ""
"The primary part is of course vBulletin forum CMS. MediaWiki with numerous "
"extensions is used for /wiki subpart. Both of these components share PHP "
"installation and MySQL database, such setup provides account integration "
"between the former two."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:39
msgid ""
"In this blog post I am going to describe how CMS work and why we should move "
"away from it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Dynamic past"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:42
msgid ""
"Site authors have always wanted to author and publish content without much "
"hassle."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:44
msgid ""
"Back in 2000s we had no swiss army knife browsers with JavaScript, modern "
"CSS, web frameworks et al. So Content Management Systems were "
"conceived. Based on PHP and MySQL, these monsters provide owner with a "
"database engine. All content is stored internally; web page is generated on "
"every single request."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:46
msgid ""
"It did its job then, and does today. Adding and modifying content is very "
"easy for both owner and end user. Deployment does not require significant "
"expertise. Simply put, you don't have to fire up an IDE or text editor "
"because all configuration and authoring is done online with neat "
"interface. This is how CMS became dominant in the wild."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:48
msgid "Yet they have their own pitfalls. Sometimes nightmares. Read on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:51
msgid ""
"The vast majority of content management systems (incl. vBulletin) require a "
"database engine, usually MySQL for data storage. It is faster than plain "
"text files and allows for more end user interactivity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:53
msgid ""
"The latter part comes with a very hefty price. Ever heard of "
"https://www.netsparker.com/blog/web-security/sql-injection-vulnerability-history/['SQL "
"injection']? Say, access a specially crafted link and you make the database "
"engine execute the wrong code. It is one of the top online vulnerabilities "
"today. And do you know how this became known to the public? You guessed "
"it. "
"http://www.zdnet.com/article/over-1-million-wordpress-websites-at-risk-from-sql-injection/[Wordpress]. "
"http://www.bbc.com/news/technology-29846539[Drupal]. In short, content "
"management systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:55
msgid ""
"There're other exploits: "
"http://krebsonsecurity.com/2013/08/simple-hack-threatens-oudated-joomla-sites/[Joomla]. "
"*http://krebsonsecurity.com/2013/10/thousands-of-sites-hacked-via-vbulletin-hole/[vBulletin]*. "
"CMS are just too bloated, complex to maintain and therefore buggy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:57
msgid ""
"Speaking of our software, right now I am aware of several 0-day "
"vulnerabilities that could break website database "
"instantly. Pop. Nothing. Error 403 or 404 instead of years of RoR history."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "Upkeep"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:60
msgid ""
"As I have already mentioned dynamic websites require a database engine, "
"usually MySQL. Not every hosting service can provide you with that."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:62
msgid ""
"And even if they do, you need to do maintenance work regularly, update. This "
"consumes our precious time we could spend on improving the game itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "Flexibility"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:65
msgid ""
"Clothes make the man. If you manage to catch the eye of a potential user, "
"you have the following, if you don't then my condolences."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:67
msgid ""
"To do that on the Internet one must have a modern, nice looking, "
"professionally done and informative home page. It's the `/` that tells the "
"players basic 80% about the game. And unless it stands out from the crowd of "
"thousands of such 'home's your average web surfer will skip it to never "
"return."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:69
msgid ""
"What do we have today? A wall of text that really looks like a long forum "
"post. A huge paragraph. Then another one. And another. Then a bullet "
"list. Afterwards a video. And... that's it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:71
msgid ""
"Nothing strange as the whole website is based on forum software. It may be "
"robust and flexible as a forum, true, but really, really not as anything "
"else. Not as home, not even as a blog."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:73
msgid ""
"Home page is almost always custom made, hand-crafted by web designer. This "
"is exactly what CMS are *not* able to provide."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:76
msgid "'''' This is unacceptable so it's time to move on. Here's what awaits you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "Everything old is new again"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:79
msgid ""
"Back in 1990s all websites were coded by hand. Yes, fire up the text editor "
"and type, type, type."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:81
msgid ""
"Handcrafted website creation has never been easier than today, in 2015. Now "
"we have rapid templating, light markup and website generators. There is no "
"need for huge databases for most of the tasks anymore."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:83
msgid "So, behold, the https://rigsofrods.github.io[new home page]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "100% static"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:86
msgid ""
"No databases, no CMS. All content is created once at build time. Hence the "
"site is *fast*, *secure* and *flexible*. JavaScript and browser features are "
"used where we need interactivity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "The look of 2015"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pregen/source/blog/2015-07-07-coming-soon-new-home-page-and-wiki/index.adoc:89
msgid "This home page actually stands out and catches the visitor's eye."
msgstr ""

